Introduction

This dataset is a collection of personal information collected from an Oura ring, which is a wearable bio tracker that collects data on sleep, heart rate, breathing rate, body temperature, and activity. Oura software uses this information to calculate scores that are meant to inform the user of their sleep quality and how it effects their other bio metrics. This ring was worn daily for 221 days.

how many observations per categorical group?

library(tidyverse)
library(readr)

biotrends <- read_csv("~/HW SDS 322E/project2/oura_2020-12-05_2021-12-05_trends.csv")

# remove scores, NA values, and days with non-wear time
biotrends <- biotrends %>% select(-c(2:9, 20:22, 28:34, 48:56)) %>% 
    na.omit() %>% filter(`Non-wear Time` == 0)

bioanalysis <- biotrends %>% select(c(4:5, 10, 14:16, 20, 28))

# create binary var
bioanalysis <- bioanalysis %>% mutate(Temperature = ifelse(`Temperature Deviation (C)` > 
    0, "Increase", "Decrease")) %>% select(-5)

Linear Classifier

# may not need this
bio_glm <- bioanalysis %>% mutate(Temp = ifelse(Temperature == 
    "Increase", 1, 0))

# fit linear model to temperature calculated by vars
fit <- glm(Temp ~ `REM Sleep Time` + `Awake Time` + `Sleep Latency` + 
    `Average HRV` + `Respiratory Rate` + Steps + `Average MET`, 
    data = bio_glm, family = "binomial")

# prediction scores for each Temperature calculated from vars
score <- predict(fit, type = "response")

# compute scores for glm
class_diag(score, truth = bio_glm$Temp, positive = 1)
##           acc  sens  spec    ppv     f1    ba    auc
## Metrics 0.733 0.589 0.835 0.7167 0.6466 0.712 0.7811
# confusion matrix increases are more likely to be predicted
# by this model
table(truth = bioanalysis$Temperature, prediction = score > 0.5)
##           prediction
## truth      FALSE TRUE
##   Decrease    86   17
##   Increase    30   43
# cross-validation of linear classifier here w/ folds
k = 10  #choose number of folds
data <- bio_glm[sample(nrow(bio_glm)), ]  #randomly order rows
folds <- cut(seq(1:nrow(bio_glm)), breaks = k, labels = F)  #create 10 folds
diags <- NULL
for (i in 1:k) {
    ## Create training and test sets
    train <- data[folds == i, ]
    test <- data[folds == i, ]
    truth <- test$Temp
    ## Train model on training set
    fit <- glm(Temp ~ (.)^2, data = train, family = "binomial")
    probs <- predict(fit, newdata = test, type = "response")
    ## Test model on test set (save all k results)
    diags <- rbind(diags, class_diag(probs, truth, positive = 1))
}

summarize_all(diags, mean)
##   acc sens spec ppv f1 ba auc
## 1   1    1    1   1  1  1   1
